description: Jade Power Trust engages in renewable energy business in Romania, other countries in Europe, and internationally. The company generates and sells electricity to electricity buyers. It owns and operates two wind projects with a total capacity of 62 megawatts (MW), two photovoltaic solar power production plants with a total capacity of 16.6 MW, and two hydro-electric generation facilities with a total capacity of 2.39 MW. The company was formerly known as Blockchain Power Trust and changed its name to Jade Power Trust in October 2019. The company was founded in 2014 and is headquartered in Toronto, Canada.
